457p-3897a1.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="800" width="1200"><media:credit>NBC; AP; Getty Images file</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A split composite image of Ro Khanna, left, Bernie Sanders, and Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez</media:text><media:description type="plain">Rep. Ro Khanna, D-Calif.; Sen. Bernie Sanders, I-Vt.; Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, D-N.Y.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260503-ro-khanna-bernie-sanders-alexandria-ocasio-cortez-vl-457p-3897a1.jpg" height="800" width="1200"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Mon, 04 May 2026 09:16:41 GMT</pubDate><title>Who will own the Bernie Sanders lane in 2028?</title><updateDate>Mon, 04 May 2026 09:16:41 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Mon, 04 May 2026 11:24:54 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>A suspected hantavirus outbreak on a cruise ship has left three people dead and another person in intensive care. The ship is currently docked in the Atlantic Ocean off the coast of West Africa, and the operating company says passengers, including the two still on board believed to have the virus, have not been allowed to get off the boat. NBC’s Camila Bernal reports for TODAY.</description><expires>2056-05-04T11:24:20.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">tdy_news_7a_bernal_hantavirus_cruise_outbreak_260504</guid><link>https://www.today.com/video/cruise-ship-hit-with-rare-hantavirus-outbreak-leaving-3-dead-262639685716</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/tdy_news_7a_bernal_hantavirus_cruise_outbreak_260504/1/abs/index.m3u8" medium="video"><media:credit></media:credit><media:title>Suspected Hantavirus Outbreak on Cruise Ship Leaves 3 Dead</media:title><media:player url="https://www.today.com/video/cruise-ship-hit-with-rare-hantavirus-outbreak-leaving-3-dead-262639685716"></media:player><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/